5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-future-will-not-be-free-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efuture%20of%20AI%20technologies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20three%20things%20are%20becoming%20more%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20AI%20is%20likely%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-at-risk-from-ai-replace-change-chatgpt-generative-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20or%20change%20millions%20of%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20It's%20likely%20going%20to%20make%20some%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-productivity-boost-job-performance-inequality-economics-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20It's%20likely%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-disruption-ai-future-careers-blue-collar-desk-work-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereplace%20some%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20million-dollar%20question%20is%2C%20how%20many%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20see%20the%20positive%20and%20negative%20impacts%20of%20AI%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty%20percent%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20Americans%20worked%20in%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20exposure%26quot%3B%20jobs%20that%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20adoption%20of%20AI%20technologies%2C%20according%20to%20a%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FERP-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereleased%20in%20March%20by%20the%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20authors%20weren't%20suggesting%20that%2020%25%20of%20Americans%20were%20likely%20to%20see%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-jobs-at-risk-replacement-artificial-intelligence-ai-labor-trends-2023-02%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejobs%20replaced%20by%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20because%20AI-related%20job%20changes%20could%20impact%20one%20job%20task%20but%20leave%20all%20others%20untouched.%20Additionally%2C%20these%20changes%20could%20bring%20about%20positive%20outcomes%20for%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20if%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-reduce-employee-headcount-this-year-ceo-study-jobcuts-efficiency-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhen%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20AI%20job%20replacement%20does%20come%2C%20some%20workers%20could%20be%20more%20at%20risk%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20workers%20typically%20benefit%20from%20technological%20change%2C%20either%20because%20the%20evolving%20technology%20provides%20new%20labor%20market%20opportunities%20for%20them%20or%20because%20it%20enhances%20their%20productivity%20in%20their%20current%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20council%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BConversely%2C%20some%20are%20harmed%2C%20typically%20due%20to%20job%20displacement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20council's%20findings%20highlight%20what%20could%20be%20a%20reality%20of%20the%20coming%20AI%20boom%3A%20It'll%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-boom-share-profits-workers-productivity-wages-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20for%20some%20workers%20and%20bad%20for%20others%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20adoption%20of%20AI%20technologies%20could%20help%20some%20workers%20become%20more%20productive%2C%20spend%20less%20time%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-generative-ai-tool-copilot-can-help-attend-fewer-meetings-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboring%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20earn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhinge-meta-nvidia-amazon-walmart-offering-high-salaries-ai-jobs-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20even%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-chatgpt-ai-make-4-day-workweek-possible-in-future-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour-day%20workweek%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20others%20could%20face%20more%20competition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-at-risk-replaced-ai-chatgpt-oxford-economist-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearn%20lower%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20even%20see%20AI%20replace%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELower-wage%20jobs%20could%20be%20at%20the%20most%20risk%20of%20being%20replaced%20by%20AI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20didn't%20highlight%20specific%20jobs%20or%20industries%20that%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20negatively%20impacted%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20council%20wrote%20that%20workers%20at%20the%20highest%20risk%20of%20replacement%20fit%20two%20criteria%3A%20Their%20jobs%20were%20highly%20exposed%20to%20AI%20and%20had%20lower%20%26quot%3Bperformance%20requirements%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20their%20job%20tasks%20had%20a%20lower%20degree%20of%20%26quot%3Bdifficulty%20or%20complexity%26quot%3B%20that%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20automated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20percent%20of%20US%20workers%20fit%20both%20criteria%2C%20the%20council%20found.%20They%20tended%20to%20be%20lower-income%20workers%20without%20a%20college%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20%26quot%3Bsuggest%20that%20AI%20may%20be%20a%20skill-biased%20technology%2C%20increasing%20relative%20demand%20for%20workers%20with%20high%20levels%20of%20education%20in%20high-earning%20occupations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20council%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20also%20suggest%20that%20AI%20could%20exacerbate%20aggregate%20income%20inequality%20if%20it%20substitutes%20for%20employment%20in%20lower-wage%20jobs%20and%20complements%20higher-wage%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20counterintuitively%2C%20the%20council%20found%20that%20the%20cohort%20of%20workers%20whose%20jobs%20had%20among%20the%20highest%20exposure%20to%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20people%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20were%20the%20least%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20high-exposure%20job%20with%20low-performance%20requirements%2C%20the%20combination%20of%20roles%20at%20most%20risk%20of%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-one%20percent%20of%20people%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20worked%20in%20jobs%20that%20are%20highly%20exposed%20to%20AI%2C%20the%20council%20found.%20However%2C%20only%206%25%20worked%20in%20high-exposure%20jobs%20that%20also%20have%20low%20performance%20requirements.%20Conversely%2C%2017%25%20of%20high%20school%20graduates%20had%20jobs%20with%20high%20AI%20exposure%2C%20and%2014%25%20had%20jobs%20with%20both%20high%20AI%20exposure%20and%20low%20performance%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20college-educated%20workers%20could%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20see%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-chatgpt-at-work-job-save-time-ai-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproductivity%20benefits%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rather%20than%20see%20their%20jobs%20replaced%20by%20these%20technologies%2C%20the%20council%20theorized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2020%25%20of%20women%20had%20jobs%20that%20are%20highly%20exposed%20to%20AI%2C%20compared%20to%2019%25%20of%20men.%20Twelve%20percent%20of%20women%20had%20jobs%20that%20fit%20both%20the%20high%20exposure%20and%20low%20performance%20requirement%20criteria%2C%20compared%20to%209%25%20of%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20isn't%20black-and-white%2C%20so%20it's%20unlikely%20AI's%20impacts%20on%20workers%20will%20be%20either.%20That%20means%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20every%20worker%20whose%20job%20is%20changed%20due%20to%20AI%20will%20be%20able%20to%20be%20clearly%20placed%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20change%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bbad%20change%26quot%3B%20bucket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20council%20cited%20the%20hypothetical%20example%20of%20a%20school%20bus%20that%20can%20drive%20itself%2C%20which%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20could%20render%20a%20bus%20driver's%20job%20obsolete.%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20the%20bus%20would%20likely%20need%20an%20adult%20on%20the%20bus%20to%20supervise%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI-led%20automation%20might%20fundamentally%20change%20the%20school%20bus%20driver's%20job%2C%20but%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20eliminate%20the%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20council%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20example%2C%20the%20bus%20driver%20gets%20to%20keep%20their%20job%20%E2%80%94%20a%20good%20outcome%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20nature%20of%20their%20job%20has%20changed%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20economic%20changes%20tend%20to%20help%20some%20workers%20and%20hurt%20others%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20first%20major%20shift%20in%20the%20global%20economy%20to%20have%20divergent%20impacts%20on%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20China%20emerged%20as%20a%20major%20player%20in%20global%20trade%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20some%20economists%20argued%20that%20the%20deluge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmake-college-housing-healthcare-childcare-more-affordable-abundance-agenda-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow-cost%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20net%20positive%20for%20the%20US%2C%20even%20though%20some%20domestic%20manufacturing%20jobs%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-manufacturing-factories-save-america-economy-future-crappy-service-jobs-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20in%20the%20process%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20lost%20their%20jobs%20lose%20money%20to%20the%20China%20shock%2C%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20get%20cheap%20goods%20at%20Walmart%20and%20Target%20or%20whatever