20street%20with%20money%20falling%20out%20of%20his%20suitcase%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6619a17d3f923f7dab07ad84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMarco%20Bottigelli%2FGetty%2C%20Yevgen%20Romanenko%2FGetty%2C%20Maskot%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20hordes%20of%20Americans%20began%20fleeing%20big%20coastal%20cities%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I've%20been%20wondering%20when%20%E2%80%94%20or%20if%20%E2%80%94%20they'd%20return.%20Sure%2C%20things%20are%20less%20expensive%20in%20the%20places%20they%20moved%20to%2C%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20is%20often%20higher.%20But%20more%20and%20more%2C%20urban%20refugees%20have%20been%20pining%20for%20the%20things%20they%20left%20behind%2C%20from%20culinary%20excellence%20to%20cultural%20diversity.%20Every%20week%20it%20seems%20like%20I%20see%20a%20new%20story%20about%20some%20former%20San%20Franciscan%20or%20New%20Yorker%20regretting%20their%20decision%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20recently%2C%20when%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20released%20its%20new%20estimates%20for%20domestic%20migration%2C%20I%20thought%20we%20were%20finally%20going%20to%20see%20a%20reversal%20of%20the%20big-city%20exodus.%20But%20I%20was%20wrong.%20From%20mid-2022%20to%20mid-2023%2C%20the%20bleeding%20in%20many%20big%20metropolitan%20areas%20continued.%20New%20York%20lost%20238%2C000%20more%20people%20than%20it%20gained.%20The%20numbers%20read%20like%20casualty%20reports%3A%20155%2C000%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%2054%2C000%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%2025%2C000%20in%20Seattle.%20Granted%2C%20the%20urban%20flight%20isn't%20as%20bad%20as%20the%20crisis-level%20hemorrhaging%20we%20saw%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20every%20day%2C%20hundreds%20and%20hundreds%20of%20people%20continue%20to%20forsake%20America's%20greatest%20cities%20for%20smaller%2C%20more%20affordable%20destinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20heard%20a%20lot%20about%20how%20the%20mass%20migration%20has%20been%20bad%20for%20major%20cities%2C%20sending%20them%20into%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-doom-loop-fix-american-city-housing-transit-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoom%20loop%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20empty%20offices%20and%20shuttered%20storefronts.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32250%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20coauthored%20by%20Enrico%20Moretti%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20thinkers%20on%20the%20geography%20of%20jobs%2C%20highlights%20the%20dangers%20the%20migration%20poses%20for%20the%20very%20professionals%20who%20are%20ditching%20big%20cities.%20Moving%20away%20from%20a%20major%20city%2C%20Moretti%20found%2C%20can%20be%20terrible%20for%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoretti%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Berkeley%2C%20followed%20workers%20whose%20companies%20shut%20down%20between%202010%20and%202017.%20How%20people%20fared%20after%20that%20depended%20on%20where%20they%20lived.%20Those%20who%20lived%20in%20small%20labor%20markets%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job%20within%20a%20year%20than%20those%20in%20large%20labor%20markets.%20To%20get%20back%20on%20their%20feet%20professionally%2C%20those%20in%20small%20markets%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20forced%20to%20relocate%20for%20employment.%20They%20were%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20settle%20for%20a%20role%20that%20was%20misaligned%20with%20their%20college%20degree%2C%20or%20in%20an%20entirely%20different%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20takeaway%20is%20that%20market%20size%20matters%2C%26quot%3B%20Moretti%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20clear%20that%20larger%20markets%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20match.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20precisely%20why%20workers%20and%20the%20companies%20that%20employ%20them%20tend%20to%20cluster%20in%20the%20same%20cities.%20Economists%20call%20it%20agglomeration.%20Let's%20say%20you're%20a%20coder%20specializing%20in%20AI.%20You're%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20find%20a%20job%20in%20San%20Francisco%20than%20you%20are%20pretty%20much%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20world%2C%20because%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20AI-related%20companies%20there.%20And%20it's%20because%20AI%20specialists%20flock%20to%20San%20Francisco%20that%20AI%20businesses%20set%20up%20shop%20there%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20That's%20how%20cities%20become%20hubs%20for%20particular%20industries%2C%20like%20finance%20in%20New%20York%20and%20fashion%20in%20Paris.%20And%20that's%20why%20people%20put%20up%20with%20all%20the%20downsides%20of%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20because%20it%20increases%20their%20odds%20of%20growing%20their%20careers.%20Moretti's%20new%20paper%20confirms%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20jobs%2C%20geography%20is%20destiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20it%20seemed%20as%20though%20the%20pandemic%20had%20rewritten%20that%20rule.%20With%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-big-battle-over-work-from-home-remote-employees-salaries-pay-cut%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20professionals%20thought%20they%20could%20afford%20to%20leave%20their%20expensive%20cities%20without%20a%20risk%20to%20their%20careers.%20If%20you%20moved%20to%20Des%20Moines%20and%20wound%20up%20losing%20your%20job%2C%20you%20could%20just%20stay%20put%20and%20get%20another%20work-from-home%20gig.%20Your%20house%20might%20be%20in%20Iowa%2C%20but%20your%20job%20market%20was%20still%20back%20in%20California%20or%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20more%20and%20more%20employers%20have%20stopped%20hiring%20for%20remote%20roles.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-wfh-jobs-application-odds-tech-market-rto-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20for%20WFH%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20cratered%2C%20putting%20everyone%20who%20moved%20away%20from%20big%20cities%20at%20risk.%20If%20they%20wind%20up%20getting%20laid%20off%20or%20they%20outgrow%20their%20current%20role%2C%20living%20in%20a%20smaller%20job%20market%20is%20going%20to%20severely%20limit%20their%20career%20options.%20As%20Moretti's%20paper%20shows%2C%20they'll%20either%20(1)%20wind%20up%20unemployed%20for%20a%20long%20stretch%2C%20(2)%20be%20forced%20to%20settle%20for%20a%20local%20job%20they're%20overqualified%20for%2C%20or%20(3)%20have%20to%20make%20an%20abrupt%20and%20costly%20move%20back%20to%20the%20big%20city%20they%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoretti%20characterizes%20being%20in%20a%20large%20labor%20market%20as%20%26quot%3Binsurance%26quot%3B%20against%20future%20shocks.%20Living%20in%20a%20big%20city%20isn't%20just%20about%20having%20a%20good%20job%20right%20now.%20It's%20what%20sets%20you%20up%20for%20success%20to%20land%20your%20next%20job%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20job%20after%20that.%20Those%20who%20moved%20away%20from%20big%20cities%20effectively%20gave%20up%20their%20career%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20not%20all%20they%20gave%20up.%20When%20you%20live%20in%20an%20industry%20hub%2C%20you're%20surrounded%20by%20professional%20peers%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20you%20to%20accumulate%20knowledge%20and%20skills.%20That's%20not%20just%20because%20you%20get%20to%20collaborate%20in%20person%20with%20your%20coworkers%20every%20day.%20In%20a%20big%20city%2C%20you%20also%20run%20into%20people%20who%20work%20for%20%3Cem%3Eother%3C%2Fem%3E%20companies%20in%20your%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20bus%2C%20at%20the%20bar%2C%20in%20line%20at%20the%20deli.%20Those%20serendipitous%20conversations%20not%20only%20expand%20your%20professional%20network%2C%20they%20also%20create%20what%20economists%20refer%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bknowledge%20spillovers%2C%26quot%3B%20helping%20you%20learn%20new%20stuff%20that's%20relevant%20to%20your%20work.%20That's%20why%20innovation%2C%20as%20measured%20by%20patents%2C%20is%20higher%20in%20large%20markets%2C%20and%20why%20businesses%20in%20big%20cities%20tend%20to%20have%20higher%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20upsides%20to%20living%20in%20a%20big%20hub%20are%20less%20obvious%20than%20the%20low%20rents%20and%20nice%20homes%20that%20have%20lured%20so%20many%20professionals%20to%20smaller%20cities.%20They%20also%20take%20time%20to%20manifest%20%E2%80%94%20you%20have%20to%20lose%20your%20job%20before%20you%20realize%20how%20hard%20it%20will%20be%20to%20find%20another.%20So%20professionals%20haven't%20come%20to%20grips%20yet%20with%20what%20they%20gave%20up%20by%20moving%20away.%20%26quot%3BThe%20benefits%20of%20being%20a%20big%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Moretti%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bhave%20been%20underappreciated%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20I%20was%20one%20of%20those%20underappreciators.%20In%202021%2C%20my%20remote%20job%20allowed%20me%20to%20move%20from%20San%20Francisco%20to%20Sacramento%20for%20my%20then-wife's%20job.%20We%20could%20suddenly%20afford%20a%20spacious%20two-bedroom%20in%20an%20apartment%20complex%20with%20a%20pool%2C%20and%20I%20loved%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20life.%20Even%20after%20we%20split%20up%2C%20my%20initial%20plan%20was%20to%20stay%20in%20Sacramento.%20But%20as%20I%20started%20driving%20into%20San%20Francisco%20more%20often%20to%20meet%20with%20sources%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20being%20in%20the%20city%20was%20helping%20me%20come%20up%20with%20better%20story%20ideas.%20So%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20Bay%20Area.%20Being%20here%20makes%20me%20better%20at%20my%20job.%20And%20if%20I%20should%20lose%20my%20job%20at%20some%20point%2C%20I%20know%20my%20search%20will%20go%20much%20better%20here%2C%20where%20there%20are%20more%20journalism%20jobs%2C%20than%20it%20would%20if%20I%20had%20stayed%20in%20Sacramento.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20lots%20of%20professionals%20who%20left%20big%20cities%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20remote%20work%20will%20stay%20where%20they%20are%2C%20even%20if%20they%20lose%20their%20jobs.%20After%20all%2C%20one%20of%20the%20other%20trends%20spurred%20by%20the%20pandemic%20was%20the%20realization%20that%20career%20isn't%20everything.%20Plenty%20of%20people%20will%20be%20happy%20to%20settle%20for%20a%20lesser%20job%20if%20it%20means%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20sit%20in%20soul-crushing%20traffic%20and%20can%20have%20a%20big%20backyard%20for%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Moretti%20thinks%20the%20exodus%20from%20big%20cities%20is%20nearing%20an%20end.%20As%20the%20outward%20migration%20slows%2C%20he%20predicts%2C%20new%20people%20looking%20for%20career%20opportunities%20will%20flood%20into%20urban%20areas%2C%20more%20than%20making%20up%20for%20the%20people%20who%20left.%20The%20big%20hubs%20will%20resume%20agglomerating%2C%20just%20as%20they%20did%20in%20the%20decades%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20pandemic.%20Cities%2C%20in%20short%2C%20will%20be%20cities%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20a%20matter%20of%20%3Cem%3Ewhen%3C%2Fem%3E%20than%20%3Cem%3Eif%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Moretti%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20thought%20this%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20permanent%20change%20in%20the%20geography%20of%20labor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMadison%20Hoff%20contributed%20reporting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-away-big-city-bad-career-job-market-suburbs-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713174541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6619a19c1caec1275a6fe2f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com