ew%20Challenge%20In%20Its%20Multi-Front%20War%20With%20Iran%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIran's%20weekend%20attack%20on%20Israel%20with%20more%20than%20300%20missiles%20and%20drones%20marks%20a%20perilous%20turn%20for%20a%20fragile%20region.%20It%20was%20an%20unprecedented%20action%2C%20the%20first%20strike%20on%20the%20Jewish%20state%20from%20Iranian%20soil.%20Iran%20declared%20it%20a%20massive%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20with%20help%20from%20the%20US%2C%20UK%20and%20other%20allies%2C%20Israel%20stopped%20almost%20every%20one%20of%20the%20missiles%20and%20drones%20launched.%20No%20one%20was%20killed%2C%20and%20the%20damage%20minor.%20It%20too%20declared%20it%20an%20enormous%20success.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20powers%20say%20their%20rivalry%20has%20shifted.%20Iran%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20equation%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20Israel%20had%20to%20know%20it%20could%20be%20attacked%20again%3B%20Israel%20said%20it%20will%20hit%20any%20nation%20that%20attacks%20it.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGroup%20of%20Seven%20leaders%20were%20due%20to%20discuss%20the%20events%20later%20Sunday%2C%20as%20was%20Israel's%20security%20cabinet.%20Its%20allies%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20are%20eager%20for%20it%20to%20show%20restraint%2C%20and%20not%20raise%20the%20stakes%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20in%20Israel%20are%20open%20to%20that%20approach%2C%20partly%20because%20Iran's%20attack%20was%20so%20unsuccessful%2C%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20a%20quick%20show%20of%20force.%20It's%20also%20because%20after%20weeks%20of%20scorn%20from%20Washington%20over%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20war%20against%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Israelis%20felt%20a%20warm%20embrace%20once%20more.%20And%20that%20was%20comforting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael%20acted%20tonight%20for%20the%20first%20time%20as%20part%20of%20a%20coalition%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20Tamir%20Heyman%2C%20a%20former%20chief%20of%20military%20intelligence.%20%26quot%3BThat%20coalition%20is%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20day%20after%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20forces%20keeping%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20in%20office%20-%20those%20to%20his%20right%20-%20have%20a%20different%20idea.%20They%20say%20that%20if%20Israel%20doesn't%20respond%20painfully%20and%20soon%2C%20Iran%20and%20its%20proxy%20militias%20across%20the%20region%20are%20likely%20to%20see%20weakness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20we%20need%20a%20crushing%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20National%20Security%20Minister%20Itamar%20Ben%20Gvir.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20sent%20the%20missiles%20in%20retaliation%20for%20the%20April%201%20killing%20of%20Iranian%20military%20officers%20in%20Damascus%2C%20widely%20attributed%20to%2C%20but%20not%20acknowledged%20by%2C%20Israel.%20Many%20saw%20Iran's%20early%20and%20frequent%20publicizing%20of%20its%20attack%20as%20evidence%20that%20it%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20point%20rather%20than%20start%20a%20war.%20Shortly%20after%20launching%20its%20attack%2C%20Iran's%20mission%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20matter%20can%20be%20deemed%20concluded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESima%20Shine%2C%20a%20former%20research%20director%20of%20Israel's%20Mossad%20spy%20agency%2C%20said%20she%20believes%20Iran%20took%20into%20consideration%20Israel's%20air%20defence%20system%20and%20wasn't%20looking%20to%20inflict%20major%20casualties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Israeli%20military%20spokesmen%20said%20the%20arrival%20of%20more%20than%20100%20ballistic%20missiles%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20attack%20was%20not%20an%20act%20of%20theater%3B%20they%20could%20have%20caused%20enormous%20death%20and%20destruction%20if%20Israel%20didn't%20have%20such%20an%20advanced%20air%20defence%20system%20and%20a%20strong%20set%20of%20alliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20any%20disagreement%20over%20how%20to%20proceed%20stems%20from%20the%20difference%20between%20how%20the%20Saturday%20night%20attack%20is%20seen%2C%20whether%20a%20retaliation%20for%20Damascus%20or%20part%20of%20Iran's%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20make%20life%20unbearable%20for%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%20in%20Israel%2C%20Iran%20is%20the%20puppet%20master%20of%20its%20regional%20foes%2C%20starting%20first%20and%20foremost%20with%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Islamist%20Palestinian%20group%20that%20attacked%20it%20in%20October%2C%20killing%201%2C200%20and%20abducting%20250%20more%2C%20threatening%20the%20country%20to%20its%20very%20core.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20responded%20with%20an%20unforgiving%20war%20that%20is%20still%20underway.%20Some%2033%2C000%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20according%20to%20Hamas%2C%20considered%20a%20terrorist%20organization%20by%20the%20US%20and%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20100%20hostages%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20freed%20and%20thousands%20of%20Hamas%20fighters%20are%20still%20entrenched%20in%20the%20southern%20Gaza%20city%20of%20Rafah.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAvi%20Melamed%2C%20a%20former%20Israeli%20intelligence%20officer%20who's%20written%20extensively%20on%20Iran%2C%20said%20he%20hopes%20that%20after%20the%20Iranian%20attack%2C%20the%20US%20will%20be%20more%20sympathetic%20to%20Israel's%20insistence%20on%20attacking%20Rafah%20and%20dismantling%20Hamas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Hamas%20sees%20Iran's%20attack%20and%20thinks%20it%20is%20still%20going%20to%20stay%20on%20its%20feet%2C%20that%20is%20bad%20news%20for%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinance%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotrich%20made%20a%20similar%20point%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20time%20to%20learn%20lessons%2C%20change%20direction%2C%20continue%20to%20Rafah%20now%20and%20restore%20full%20Israeli%20control%20all%20over%20Gaza.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20been%20warning%20against%20such%20an%20operation%20because%20of%20the%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20civilians%20sheltering%20in%20Rafah%20and%20the%20growing%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20Gaza.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamas%20just%20rejected%20Israel's%20latest%20offer%20for%20a%20cease-fire%20and%20exchange%20of%20hostages%20for%20prisoners%2C%20further%20evidence%20for%20some%20that%20Iran's%20allies%20are%20feeling%20emboldened%20rather%20than%20frightened.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Amos%20Yadlin%2C%20a%20former%20director%20of%20Israeli%20military%20intelligence%20who%20advises%20opposition%20leader%20and%20war%20cabinet%20member%20Benny%20Gantz%2C%20sees%20it%20differently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLast%20night's%20attack%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20strategic%20change%20in%20the%20war%20and%20even%20to%20its%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHamas%20has%20been%20beaten%20hard%20enough%2C%20Israel%20can%20now%20agree%20to%20a%20deal%20on%20the%20return%20of%20all%20its%20hostages%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20permanent%20cease-fire%20and%20withdrawal%20from%20Gaza%20and%20win%20back%20its%20international%20legitimacy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20dilemma%20for%20Israel%20is%20its%20northern%20border%20with%20Lebanon%20where%20it's%20fighting%20Iran-backed%20Hezbollah%2C%20and%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20civilians%20on%20both%20sides%20have%20been%20forced%20out%20of%20their%20homes.%20Israel%20sees%20Iran%20behind%20this%20conflict%20as%20well%20and%20says%20it%20must%20be%20able%20to%20return%20its%20citizens%20to%20their%20homes%20-%20either%20by%20diplomacy%20or%20by%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20as%20it%20contemplates%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20Iran's%20attack%2C%20Israel%20worries%20about%20not%20only%20its%20enemy%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20away%20but%20also%20those%20right%20on%20its%20borders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3